## Worker Node — implementación de tools

Añadir tools al array de tools del `ConversationWorker`:

```ts
const EVENT_TOOLS: StandardTool[] = [
  {
    name: 'get_events',
    description: 'Lista los eventos del usuario',
    parameters: {
      type: 'object',
      properties: {
        type: { type: 'string' },
        status: { type: 'string', enum: ['active', 'cancelled', 'completed'] },
        from: { type: 'string', description: 'ISO 8601 date' },
        to:   { type: 'string', description: 'ISO 8601 date' },
      }
    }
  },
  {
    name: 'create_event',
    description: 'Crea un evento con sus disparos de recordatorio',
    parameters: {
      type: 'object',
      required: ['content', 'event_at', 'type', 'reminders'],
      properties: {
        content:         { type: 'string' },
        event_at:        { type: 'string', description: 'ISO 8601 UTC' },
        event_end:       { type: 'string', description: 'ISO 8601 UTC, solo para bloques con duración' },
        type:            { type: 'string' },
        recurrence_rule: { type: 'string', description: 'iCal RRULE, ej: FREQ=WEEKLY;BYDAY=MO' },
        reminders: {
          type: 'array',
          items: {
            type: 'object',
            required: ['offset', 'message'],
            properties: {
              offset:  { type: 'string', description: 'Offset relativo, ej: "-1 day", "-7 days", "0"' },
              message: { type: 'string' }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }
  },
  // update_event, cancel_event, snooze_event — mismo patrón
]
```

Cada tool llama a `LaravelClient` en el endpoint correspondiente y retorna el resultado como `tool_result`.

